<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI INT'L MACHINE TOOL SHOW DRAWS OVER 4,100 FOREIGN BUYERS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 20 (CNA) 03/20/07  20:13:47 (By Nick Huang)
</P>
<P>
The just-concluded Taipei International Machine Tool Show
attracted 4,180 foreign visitors, Taiwan External Trade
Development Council officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The show, which was held at the Taipei World Trade Center March
12-17, drew an additional 17.7 percent, or 630 foreign buyers,
over the past year, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Among visitors making purchases during the show, Japanese were
the biggest buyers, with 566 people making a purchase, up 216
over the previous year's level, according to officials.
</P>
<P>
The number of buyers from BRIC -- a term used to refer to the
combination of Brazil, Russia, India and China -- showed a
staggering increase of 46 percent, or 523 people, over the year
past.
</P>
<P>
210 buyers were Chinese, an increase of 139; Russian buyers
numbered 87, an increase of 46; 36 Brazilian made purchases, an
increase of 10; while the number of Indian buyers decreased by
30, to 190, said officials.
</P>
